en: The Life and Exploits of the Ingenious Gentleman don Quixote de la Mancha
1.1 DQ at his library reading chivalric novels

Don Quixote, dressed as a 18th century English gentleman, reads peacefully while he observes his family arms (over the fireplace); these, far from looking like "tomadas de orín y llenas de moho, luengos siglos había, que estaban puestas y olvidadas en un rincón" (1:1), appear new and neat.Drawing and engraving are quite acceptable.
1 - Turned copy after London: Tonson, 1738.2 - Plate 1.
Scrutiny of don Quixote's library and housekeeper's fears

In the center of the composition, the housekeeper, who "tornó luego con una escudilla de agua bendita, y un hisopo, y dijo: Tome vuestra Merced, Señor Licenciado, rocíe este aposento, no esté aquí algún encantador de los muchos que tienen estos libros, y nos encanten" (6:1); the priest, the niece and the barber listen to her.Drawing and engraving are quite acceptable.
1 - Turned copy after London: Tonson, 1738.2 - Plate 2.
14.1 Episode of Grisóstomo and Marcela, continuation14.3 Marcela’s appearance and speech14.4 Burial of Grisóstomo

During Grisóstomo's burial (center of the composition), Marcela appears over a boulder; Ambrosio, Grisóstomo's friend, reprimands her.Also in the scene,don Quixote, Sancho Panza and several shepherds.Drawing and engraving are quite acceptable, but clumsy.
1 - Turned copy after London: Tonson, 1738.2 - Plate 3.
The innkeeper´s wife, her daughter and Maritornes take care of don Quixote
16.1 DQ and SP arrival at second inn

The scene includes the figures of don Quixote, the innkeeper's wife and her daughter, Maritornes, and Sancho complaining about his own pain too.Accurate composition to Cervantes' text. "En esta maldita cama se acostó Don Quixote, y luego la ventera, y su hija le emplastaron de arriba a abajo, alumbrándoles Maritornes" (16:1).Drawing and engraving are clumsy.
1 - Turned copy after London: Tonson, 1738.2 - Plate 4.
Don Quixote asks the galley slaves about their crimes
Don Quixote talking to the galley slaves (dialogue) about their crimes; also in the scene, Sancho.Drawing and engraving are acceptable.
1 - Turned copy after London: Tonson, 1738.2 - Plate 5.
Dorotea is surprised by the priest, Cardenio and the barber
28.1 Priest, barber and Cardenio encounter Dorotea
Dorotea, washing her feet in a stream, is discovered by the priest, the barber and Cardenio in Sierra Morena.This scene will be habitual in future editions.Drawing and engraving are poor.
1 - Turned copy after London: Tonson, 1738.2 - Plate 6.
34.1 Reading of El curioso impertinente continues

Camila pretends to stab herself and Lotario and Leonela try to stop her; Anselmo, her husband, is hidden behind a tapestry (he should remain behind the tapestry during the whole scene).Drawing and engraving are quite acceptable.
1 - Turned copy after London: Tonson, 1738.2 - Plate 7.
